{"type":null,"faqId":41705,"title":"What can I do if my phone can't be detected by Bluetooth?","answer":"<html>\n<head>\n<META http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=UTF-8\">\n<style type=\"text/css\">.b1{white-space-collapsing:preserve;}\n.d1{margin: 1.18125in 0.7875in 1.18125in 0.7875in;}\n.s1{display: inline-block; text-indent: 0; min-width: 0.3048611in;}\n.p1{text-indent:-0.2951389in;margin-left:1.4763889in;margin-top:0.055555556in;margin-bottom:0.055555556in;text-align:start;hyphenate:auto;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;}\n</style>\n</head>\n<body class=\"b1\">\n<div  >\n<p  >\n<span class=\"s1\">1.  </span><span>Go to the Bluetooth settings screen and check whether the visibility has expired. If it expires, set a proper time period and search for the Bluetooth again.</span>\n</p>\n<p  >\n<span class=\"s1\">1.  </span><span>Check whether the two phones have paired.</span>\n</p>\n<p  >\n<span class=\"s1\">1.  </span><span>If the Bluetooth can't be detected after you have performed the preceding steps, restore the phone to factory settings or clean up the user data.</span>\n</p>\n<p  >\n<span class=\"s1\">1.  </span><span>If the problem persists, it may be caused by the hardware failure. Go to your local Huawei service center to test the hardware.</span>\n</p>\n</div>\n</body>\n</html>\n","faqTypeId":null,"faqType":null,"useful":0,"unUseful":0,"languageId":244,"languageName":"mm","faqCode":"7165","faqTypeCode":null,"isTop":"0","moduleCode":"faq","productId":null,"productCode":null,"postDate":1442207746000,"seriesProductName":"RIO-L01","visitedTimes":1,"isUsefulFlag":null,"score":0,"times":0,"imageList":null,"displayType":"text","justView":"0","fileName":null,"filePath":null,"imagePath":null,"imageName":null,"productIdList":null,"curPage":null,"pageSize":null,"siteCode":null,"statusFlag":"Publish","returnCode":0,"totalRows":null,"keywords":"RIO-L01, G7 plus","avgScore":0.0,"createDate":null,"totalPages":null}